### 🎯 Objectives
By the end of this midterm project, students will be able to:
1. Derive and mathematically prove the Inverse Kinematics (IK) solution for the Spartan Robokit.
2. Develop a custom Python-based calculator to compute Inverse Kinematics and visualize the manipulator's workspace.
3. Integrate Inverse Kinematics algorithms into MATLAB to establish a functioning digital twin that controls the physical Spartan Robokit.
4. Experimentally validate the IK model by performing position vector tests and evaluating the physical spatial accuracy using measuring tools.
5. Analyze and classify computational IK outputs to determine their operational validity (e.g., identifying mirrored or undefined configurations).

